2.9.1 Transforming Records for Modelling and Analysis

############################Table 2.4/2.9.1 Transforming Records for Modelling and Analysis
table_funct=function(table){
    table$ageat_Comm_date=as.numeric(difftime(as.POSIXct(Commencement_date), as.POSIXct(Date_of_bitht, tz="UTC"), units="days")/365.242)
    table$ageat_End_date=as.numeric(difftime(as.POSIXct(End_date), as.POSIXct(Date_of_bitht, tz="UTC"), units="days")/365.242)
    table$ageat_Model_start_date=as.numeric(difftime(as.POSIXct(Model_start_date), as.POSIXct(Date_of_bitht, tz="UTC"), units="days")/365.242)
    table$ageat_Model_end_date=as.numeric(difftime(as.POSIXct(Model_end_date), as.POSIXct(Date_of_bitht, tz="UTC"), units="days")/365.242)

    table$xi=pmax(table$ageat_Comm_date,table$ageat_Model_start_date,Model_start_age)
    table$xiplusti=pmin(table$ageat_End_date,table$ageat_Model_end_date,Model_end_age)
    table$di=ifelse(table$xiplusti < table$ageat_End_date,0,1)
    table$Comments=ifelse(table$xi > table$xiplusti,"Excluded as no time lived to contribute to model",table$xiplusti-table$xi)
    return(table)
}

############################Life table
n=range(ceiling(data$EntAge+data$TObs))
k=n[2]-n[1]+1
Ex_c=c()
dx=c()
Ex=c()
for(i in 1:k){
  
  newdata <- subset(data, (data$EntAge<(60+i)  &  data$EntAge>=(60+i-1)) | ( (data$EntAge+data$TObs-i+1)>0 & data$EntAge<(60+i) & data$EntAge+data$TObs>=(60+i-1)),
                    select=c(Status,TObs,EntAge))
  
  t=ifelse((newdata$EntAge<(60+i)  &  newdata$EntAge>=(60+i-1)),(ifelse((newdata$TObs+newdata$EntAge)>=(60+i),(60+i)-newdata$EntAge,newdata$TObs)),ifelse((newdata$TObs+newdata$EntAge-(60+i-1))>=1,1,(newdata$TObs+newdata$EntAge-(60+i-1))))
  d=sum(ifelse(newdata$Status==1  &  ((newdata$EntAge+newdata$TObs)<(60+i) & (newdata$EntAge+newdata$TObs)>=(60+i-1)),1,0))
  Ex_c[i]=sum(t)
  dx[i]=d
  Ex[i]=nrow(newdata)
}
Ex_c=round(Ex_c,4)
x=seq(60,103,by=1)
life_table=data.frame(age_interval=paste0("(",x,",",(x+1),")"),Ex_c,dx,Ex)

5.5 Fitting the Gompertz Model

############################5.5 Fitting the GompertzTObsTObs Model
FullNegLogL=function(p,data){
  
  a=p[1]
  b=p[2]
  x=data$EntAge
  d=data$Status
  t=data$TObs
  
  sum(((exp(b*t)-1)/b)*exp(a+(b*x)))-sum(d*(a+(b*(x+t))))
}

Identifiability = function(Estimates , gradtol = 10^length(Estimates$estimate)){
  if(sum(sign(eigen(Estimates$hessian)$value))/length(eigen(Estimates$hessian)$value) ==(-1) & sum(eigen(Estimates$hessian)$value)<gradtol){
    cat('The model is Identifiable')
  }
  else{cat('The model is not Identifiable')}
}

############################Akaikes Information Criterion
AIC_funct =function(data,p){ 
  k=length(p)
  return((-2)*(-FullNegLogL(p,data))+2*k)
}
AIC_c_funct=function(data,p){ 
  k=length(p)   
  n=nrow(data)
  return(AIC_funct(data,p)+(2*k*(k+1)/(n-k-1)))
}
p=Estimates$estimate
AIC =AIC_funct(data,p)
AIC_c=AIC_c_funct(data,p)

############################The Bayesian Information Criterion
BIC_funct =function(data,p){ 
  k=length(p)
  n=nrow(data)
  return((-2)*(-FullNegLogL(p,data))+k*log(n))
}
BIC =BIC_funct(data,p)

############################Poisson deviance residual_rj
rj_Calc = function(data){
  
  Estimates = nlm(FullNegLogL , p = c(-10 , 0.1),data , typsize = c(-10 , 0.1) , gradtol = 1e-10)
  a=Estimates$estimate[1]
  b=Estimates$estimate[2]
  
  #######################################
  n=range(ceiling(data$EntAge+data$TObs))
  k=n[2]-n[1]+1
  w=c()
  landa=c()
  rj=c()
  s=0
  t2=0
  for(i in 1:k){
    
    newdata <- subset(data, (data$EntAge<(60+i)  &  data$EntAge>=(60+i-1)) | ( (data$EntAge+data$TObs-i+1)>0 & data$EntAge<(60+i) & data$EntAge+data$TObs>=(60+i-1)),
                      select=c(Status,TObs,EntAge))
    w[i]=nrow(newdata)
    
    
    t=ifelse((newdata$EntAge<(60+i)  &  newdata$EntAge>=(60+i-1)),(ifelse((newdata$TObs+newdata$EntAge)>=(60+i),(60+i)-newdata$EntAge,newdata$TObs)),ifelse((newdata$TObs+newdata$EntAge-(60+i-1))>=1,1,(newdata$TObs+newdata$EntAge-(60+i-1))))
    t2=t2+sum(t)
    x=ifelse((newdata$EntAge<(60+i)  &  newdata$EntAge>=(60+i-1)),newdata$EntAge,(60+i-1))
    
    l=(exp(b*t)-1)*exp(a+b*x)/b
    landa[i]=sum(l)
    
    d=sum(ifelse(newdata$Status==1  &  ((newdata$EntAge+newdata$TObs)<(60+i) & (newdata$EntAge+newdata$TObs)>=(60+i-1)),1,0))
    s=s+d
    
    rj[i] = sign(d - landa[i])*sqrt(2*(d*log(d/landa[i])-(d-landa[i])))
    
  }
  list( landa = landa , rj = rj , totaldeath = s , totaltimelived = t2 )
}
results=rj_Calc(data)

chisquaretest = function(rj , alpha = 0.05){
  rj = na.omit(rj)
  test_statistics = sum(rj^2)
  if( pchisq(test_statistics, length(rj) , lower.tail = F)>alpha){cat('Null hypothesis has been accepted with a p_value of' , pchisq(test_statistics, length(rj) , lower.tail = F) , ' with a test statistic of' , test_statistics)}
  else{cat('Null hypothesis has been rejected with a p_value of' , pchisq(test_statistics, length(rj) , lower.tail = F), ' with a test statistic of' , test_statistics)}
  
}

# standardized chisquare test way 1 
library(DescTools)
chisquarestandardizedtest_1 = function(rj , alpha = 0.05){
  rj = na.omit(rj)
  n=sum(complete.cases(rj))
  m=floor(n^0.5)
  test=PearsonTest(rj,n.classes=(m),adjust = FALSE)
  if( (test$p)>alpha){cat('Null hypothesis has been accepted with a p_value of' , test$p , ' with a test statistic of' , test$statistic)}
  else{cat('Null hypothesis has been rejected with a p_value of' , test$p , ' with a test statistic of' , test$statistic)}  
}
chisquarestandardizedtest_1(rj)

# standardized chisquare test way 2
chisquarestandardizedtest_2 = function(rj , include.mean_sd = c('TRUE' , 'FALSE'), alpha = 0.05){
  library(DescTools)
  rj = na.omit(rj)
  m = floor(sqrt(length(rj)))
  i=c(2:m-1)
  if(include.mean_sd=='TRUE'){
    breaks=qnorm(i/m , mean(rj) , sd(rj))
    breaks=append(breaks,(max(rj)+1))
    breaks=append(breaks,(min(rj)-1),0)
  }
  if(include.mean_sd=='FALSE'){
    breaks=qnorm(i/m)
    breaks=append(breaks,(max(rj)+1))
    breaks=append(breaks,(min(rj)-1),0)
  }
  table = cbind(Freq(rj ,breaks)[,c(1,2)] , f = length(rj)/m , expression = (Freq(rj ,breaks)$freq - length(rj)/m)^2/(length(rj)/m))
  test_statistics = sum(table$expression)
  if( pchisq(test_statistics, (m-1) , lower.tail = F)>alpha){cat('Null hypothesis has been accepted with a p_value of' , pchisq(test_statistics, (m-1) , lower.tail = F) , ' with a test statistic of' , test_statistics)}
  else{cat('Null hypothesis has been rejected with a p_value of' , pchisq(test_statistics, (m-1) , lower.tail = F), ' with a test statistic of' , test_statistics)}
  return(table)
}
table_chisq_pearson=chisquarestandardizedtest_2(rj , include.mean_sd = TRUE)

BiasTest = function(rj , alpha = 0.05){
  rj = na.omit(rj)
  test_statistics = length(which(rj>0))
  if( pbinom(test_statistics , length(rj) , 1/2)>alpha){cat('Null hypothesis has been accepted with a p_value of' ,pbinom(test_statistics , length(rj) , 1/2) , ' with a test statistic of' , test_statistics)}
  else{cat('Null hypothesis has been rejected with a p_value of' ,pbinom(test_statistics , length(rj) , 1/2), ' with a test statistic of' , test_statistics)} 
}
BiasTest(rj)

# way 3
biastest = function(rj , alpha = 0.05){
  rj = na.omit(rj)
  test_statistics = length(which(rj>0))
  return(binom.test(test_statistics , length(rj) , 1/2 , alternative = 'less',conf.level =(1-alpha)))
}

library("randtests")
KS_RunsTest = function(rj , alpha = 0.05){
  n = length(rj)
  rj = na.omit(rj)
  num_success = length(rle(sign(as.numeric(rj)))[[1]]) - 1
  if( pruns(q=num_success, n1=num_success, n2=(n-num_success), lower.tail =FALSE, log.p = FALSE)>alpha){cat('Null hypothesis has been accepted with a p_value of' ,pruns(q=num_success,
                                                                                                                                                                         n1=num_success, n2=(n-num_success), lower.tail =FALSE, log.p = FALSE) , ' with a test statistic of' , num_success)}
  else{cat('Null hypothesis has been rejected with a p_value of' ,pruns(q=num_success, n1=num_success, n2=(n-num_success), lower.tail =FALSE, log.p = FALSE), ' with a test statistic of' , num_success)}
}

# way 3 global function
lag_1_test = function(rj, alpha = 0.05){
  rj = na.omit(rj)
  n = length(rj)
  c = cor(rj[-1],rj[-n])
  Z = c*sqrt(n-1)
  if(pnorm(Z)>alpha){cat('Null hypothesis has been accepted with a p_value of' , pnorm(Z), ' with a test statistic of' , Z)}
  else{cat('Null hypothesis has been rejected with a p_value of' , pnorm(Z) , ' with a test statistic of' , Z)}
  return(data.frame(z1=sum(rj[-n])/(n-1),z2=sum(rj[-1])/(n-1),c1=c,Z=Z))
}

7.4 Proportional Hazards Model

############################7.4 Example: a Proportional Hazards Model
###code 1=gender only ,code 2=Pensions only , code 3(or else)=both
FullNegLogL_Proportional=function(p,data,code){
  a=p[1]
  b=p[2]
  if(code==1){
    zeta_1=p[3]
    zeta_2=0
  }else if(code==2){
    zeta_1=0
    zeta_2=p[3]
  }else {
    zeta_1=p[3]
    zeta_2=p[4]
  }
  
  x=data$EntAge
  d=data$Status
  t=data$TObs
  z_1=data$Gender
  z_2=data$BH
  
  sum(((exp(b*t)-1)/b)*exp(a+(b*x)+zeta_1*z_1+zeta_2*z_2))-sum(d*(a+(b*(x+t)+zeta_1*z_1+zeta_2*z_2)))
}

AIC_prop_funct =function(data,p,code){ 
  k=length(p)
  return((-2)*(-FullNegLogL_Proportional(p,data,code))+2*k)
}

8.3 The KaplanMeier Estimator

############################The Kaplan Meier and Fleming Harrington Estimator
Kaplan_Meier=function(data , baseline_age = floor(min(data$Endaage))){
  
  data$Endaage=data$EntAge+data$TObs
  data <-data[order(data$Endaage),]
  l=c()
  for(i in 1:nrow(data)){
    
    newdata <- subset(data,((data$EntAge+data$TObs)>=(data$EntAge[i]+data$TObs[i]) & (data$EntAge)<(data$EntAge[i]+data$TObs[i])),select=c(Status,TObs,EntAge))
    l[i]=nrow(newdata)
    
  }
  data$l=l
  d=c()
  for(i in 1:nrow(data)){
    
    newdata <- subset(data,((data$EntAge+data$TObs)==(data$EntAge[i]+data$TObs[i]) & data$Status==1))
    d[i]=nrow(newdata)
    
  }
  data$d=d
  
  library(dplyr)
  data=distinct(data,data$Endaage,.keep_all=TRUE)
  
  S=function(d,l){
    1-d/l
  }
  
  s_base =min(which(floor(data$Endaage) ==  baseline_age))
  
  S_age = S(data$d[s_base],data$l[s_base])
  for(i in 2:(nrow(data)-s_base+1)){
    
    S_age[i]=S_age[i-1]*S(data$d[i],data$l[i])
    
  }
  
  
  df=data.frame(data$Endaage[s_base:nrow(data)],data$l[s_base:nrow(data)],data$d[s_base:nrow(data)],S_age)
  df$tosum=df$data.d/((df$data.l-df$data.d)*df$data.l)
  S_hat=c()
  for(i in 1:nrow(df)){
    S_hat[i]=df$S[i]*sqrt(sum(df$tosum[1:i]))
  }
  df$S_hat=S_hat
  df = subset(df, select = -c(tosum) )
  if(baseline_age<data$Endaage[s_base]){df=rbind(c(baseline_age,data$l[1],0,1,0),df)}
  
  return(df)
}


Kaplan_Meier_table=function(df,baseline_age){
  colnames(df)=c(paste0("xi+ti"),paste0("lxi+ti"),paste0("dxi+ti"),paste0("S_hat_",baseline_age),"s.e")
  return(df)
}



Kaplan_Meier_plot=function(df){
  colnames(df)[1] <- c("data.Endaage")
  n=nrow(df)
  fn <- stepfun(x=df$data.Endaage[-n], y=df$S_age, f=0)
  return(fn)
}

8.5 The FlemingHarrington Estimator

Fleming_Harrington=function(data , baseline_age = floor(min(data$Endaage)) ){
  
  data$Endaage=data$EntAge+data$TObs
  data <-data[order(data$Endaage),]
  
  l=c()
  for(i in 1:nrow(data)){   
    newdata <- subset(data,((data$EntAge+data$TObs)>=(data$EntAge[i]+data$TObs[i]) & (data$EntAge)<(data$EntAge[i]+data$TObs[i])),select=c(Status,TObs,EntAge))
    l[i]=nrow(newdata)   
  }
  data$l=l
  d=c()
  for(i in 1:nrow(data)){
    
    newdata <- subset(data,((data$EntAge+data$TObs)==(data$EntAge[i]+data$TObs[i]) & data$Status==1))
    d[i]=nrow(newdata)
    
  }
  data$d=d
  
  library(dplyr)
  data=distinct(data,data$Endaage,.keep_all=TRUE)
  
  s_base =min(which(floor(data$Endaage) ==  baseline_age))
  
  
  landa=function(d,l){
    d/l
  }
  
  S_fleming=c()
  for(i in 1:(nrow(data)- s_base + 1)){
    S_fleming[i]=exp(-sum(landa(d,l)[1:i]))
  }
  
  df=data.frame(data$Endaage[s_base:nrow(data)],data$l[s_base:nrow(data)],data$d[s_base:nrow(data)],S_fleming)
  if(baseline_age<data$Endaage[s_base]){df=rbind(c(baseline_age,data$l[1],0,1),df)}
  return(df)
}
Fleming_Harrington_table=function(df,baseline_age){
  colnames(df)=c(paste0("xi+ti"),paste0("lxi+ti"),paste0("dxi+ti"),paste0("S_hat_",baseline_age))
  return(df)
}

Fleming_Harrington_plot=function(df){
  colnames(df)[1] <- c("data.Endaage")
  n=nrow(df)
  fn <- stepfun(x=df$data.Endaage[-n], y=df$S_fleming, f=0)
  return(fn)
}
